# Nexus Mods Author Tools License

## Version 1.0 

Copyright © 2026 Black Tree Gaming Ltd. (trading as Nexus Mods)

---

## 1. Purpose

The Nexus Mods Author Tools project exists to support the creation of game modifications and to strengthen the modding ecosystem on the Nexus Mods Platform.

The source code is made publicly available to encourage transparency, education, community collaboration, bug fixes, and improvements to the official Project.

The goal of this License is to encourage community collaboration while ensuring there remains a single canonical version of the Project maintained by Black Tree Gaming Ltd.

Community forks are welcomed for the purpose of contributing improvements back to the official Project.

Forks intended to create competing products, competing services, or alternative public distributions of the Project are not permitted under this License.

This License is intended to enable community participation while protecting the long-term stewardship of the Project, the investment made into its development, and the interests of the Nexus Mods Platform.

---

## 2. Definitions

**Project** means the Nexus Mods Author Tools software, including its source code, documentation, assets, user interface, architecture, workflows, configuration, and any other materials distributed as part of the official repository.

**Official Repository** means the primary source repository owned and maintained by Black Tree Gaming Ltd.

**Nexus Mods Platform** means the websites, APIs, applications, services, repositories, tooling, infrastructure, and related products owned or operated by Black Tree Gaming Ltd. under the Nexus Mods brand.

**Competing Service** means any product, service, website, application, repository, marketplace, hosted offering, platform, infrastructure, or other software whose primary purpose, in whole or in part, is to enable users to create, upload, host, browse, discover, manage, distribute, install, share, or download modifications for video games, or to provide tooling or infrastructure supporting such activities, regardless of whether that service is commercial, non-commercial, open source, source available, or proprietary.

