## 4. Restrictions

Unless expressly authorised in writing by Black Tree Gaming Ltd., you may not:

* Publish, maintain, market, or promote a fork as an alternative, replacement, successor, or competing version of the Project.
* Distribute releases, binaries, packages, installers, or other compiled or packaged versions of the Project except where reasonably necessary for contributing to the Official Repository.
* Develop, maintain, operate, or support an independent product or service based upon the Project that is intended for ongoing public use outside the Official Repository.
* Use the Project, or any substantial portion of its source code, documentation, architecture, user interface, workflows, assets, configuration, or design to develop, operate, maintain, or support a Competing Service.
* Use the Project, or any substantial portion of its source code, architecture, user interface, workflows, documentation, assets, configuration, or design as the basis for developing, designing, implementing, or supporting a substantially similar product or service that competes with the Project or the Nexus Mods Platform, regardless of whether the resulting implementation is copied directly, modified, independently reimplemented, or otherwise derived from knowledge obtained through access to the Project.
* Remove, alter, or obscure any copyright, license, attribution, or ownership notices.
* Represent modified versions or forks as official Nexus Mods software.
* Use the Nexus Mods name, logo, branding, trademarks, icons, artwork, or other visual identity except where expressly authorised in writing.

